messages.text: How many of the snakes do you have?
She must have shone her flashlight on a snake.
Em, there’s no more time. She’ll kill you next.
I’m going to the behavioral testing room!
I can lock the snakes inside.
I can hear you running for your life, kiddo.
The snakes are sensitive to bright light!
You think I'm an idiot, don’t you?
You’re just trying to stay hidden.
If you don’t show yourself, I’m gonna hunt you down.
And if the snakes don’t kill you first…
James - I locked myself and the 10 snakes in the testing room.
What will you do if she shoots out the lock?
Maybe I can wedge your bat between the door handles?
I need to lock the snakes in a cage first.
If she shines that light in here, it’s over.
Come on, Em. Hurry. You got this.
But she’s breaking through the door!
She’s firing her gun into the cage!
Wait. One of the snakes just opened the lock.
They’re all over her! What do I do?
You have to knock out the flashlight!
She will die in under two minutes.
You need to find the anti-venom.
It’s in a cabinet in the maintenance room.
Can you even see where you’re going?
Look for a glass bottle in the big cabinet.
There are syringes next to it.
It’s there in the room with you?
Okay, Em. You have about thirty seconds.
Fill a syringe with the anti-venom and give Daria the injection.
Just let me help Daria to the door.
We can’t let the light in.
I’m going to drive to the hospital and meet you.
I’m not the hero here. You are.
You saved the snakes AND Daria.
Well, she’s still going to jail.
She’ll be locked up for sure.
But the snakes don’t have to live as prisoners.
We can design a new facility for them.
Keep them in the dark, safe.
We can figure that out later.
Maybe we publish the results of the genetic tests?
Make sure this sort of thing never happens again.
I guess that’s up to you.
I still want to be with you.
I’ve always loved you too, James…
But I need you to promise me one thing.
No more keeping me in the dark.
